          <div class="text-gray-600">Cities Lyft Operates</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Lyft's History & Insurance -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-4">Understanding Lyft Accident Claims</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 text-center mb-12 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        From pink mustaches to a Lyft giant‚ÄîLyft has grown, and so have accident claims
      </p>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center mb-16">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Lyft's Journey: 2012 to Today</h3>
          <div class="space-y-4 text-gray-600">
            <p>
              <strong>2012:</strong> Lyft launched as a peer-to-peer Lyft platform, famous for its iconic pink mustaches on car grilles and the expectation that riders would fist-bump their drivers.
            </p>
            <p>
              <strong>2015:</strong> Lyft removed the pink mustaches, rebranding with the pink "amp" device. The company began offering premium services like Lyft Plus (larger vehicles) and Lyft Line (shared rides).
            </p>
            <p>
              <strong>2019:</strong> Lyft went public on the NASDAQ, valued at $24 billion. The company now operates in over 600 cities across the United States and Canada.
            </p>
            <p>
              <strong>Today:</strong> Lyft completes millions of rides daily, making accident claims increasingly common‚Äîand increasingly complex.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-50 p-8 rounded-xl">
          <h4 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Key Lyft Facts</h4>
          <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-600">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-secondary font-bold">‚úì</span>
              <span>Second-largest Lyft company in the US</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-secondary font-bold">‚úì</span>
              <span>Over 1 million active drivers</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
