              <td class="p-4">$50K/$100K/$25K</td>
              <td class="p-4">$50K/$100K/$25K</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-white">
              <td class="p-4 font-semibold">Period 2 & 3 Liability</td>
              <td class="p-4">$1,000,000</td>
              <td class="p-4">$1,000,000</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="p-4 font-semibold">Uninsured Motorist</td>
              <td class="p-4 text-green-600 font-semibold">$1M (all periods)</td>
              <td class="p-4">$1M (periods 2 & 3 only)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-white">
              <td class="p-4 font-semibold">Contingent Collision</td>
              <td class="p-4">$50K (with deductible)</td>
              <td class="p-4">$50K (with deductible)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="p-4 font-semibold">Claims Process</td>
              <td class="p-4">Via Lyft app or insurer</td>
              <td class="p-4">Via Lyft app or insurer</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      
      <div class="mt-8 bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-500 p-6 rounded-r-xl">
        <p class="text-blue-800">
          <strong>Key Difference:</strong> Lyft has historically offered uninsured motorist coverage in Period 1, while Lyft only provides it during Periods 2 and 3. This can be significant if you're hit by an uninsured driver while your Lyft driver is waiting for a ride request.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Who Can File a Claim -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-gray-900 text-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-12">Who Can File a Lyft Accident Claim?</h2>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <div class="bg-white/10 p-6 rounded-xl">
          <div class="text-4xl mb-4">üöï</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Lyft Passengers</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300">Injured while riding in a Lyft? You're protected by Lyft's $1 million insurance policy during your trip.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-white/10 p-6 rounded-xl">
          <div class="text-4xl mb-4">üöô</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Other Drivers</h3>
