        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-white/10 p-6 rounded-xl">
          <div class="text-4xl mb-4">üö∂</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Pedestrians</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300">Struck by a Lyft vehicle while walking? You may have a claim against the driver and Lyft.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-white/10 p-6 rounded-xl">
          <div class="text-4xl mb-4">üö¥</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Cyclists</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300">Hit by a Lyft while cycling? Bike accident victims often suffer serious injuries and deserve compensation.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-white/10 p-6 rounded-xl">
          <div class="text-4xl mb-4">üë§</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Lyft Drivers</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300">Lyft drivers injured on the job may have claims against other drivers or through Lyft's occupational accident coverage.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-white/10 p-6 rounded-xl">
          <div class="text-4xl mb-4">üë®‚Äçüë©‚Äçüëß</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Family Members</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300">Lost a loved one in a Lyft accident? Families can file wrongful death claims for compensation.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Lyft Driver Requirements -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-4">Lyft Driver Requirements & Safety</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 text-center mb-12 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Understanding Lyft's driver requirements can help strengthen your accident claim
      </p>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Driver Requirements</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-600">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-secondary font-bold">‚úì</span>
              <span><strong>Age:</strong> At least 21 years old (25 in some states)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-secondary font-bold">‚úì</span>
              <span><strong>License:</strong> Valid driver's license for at least 1 year</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-secondary font-bold">‚úì</span>
              <span><strong>Background Check:</strong> Criminal and driving history review</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-secondary font-bold">‚úì</span>
              <span><strong>Vehicle:</strong> Must be 2010 or newer, 4-door, pass inspection</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-secondary font-bold">‚úì</span>
              <span><strong>Insurance:</strong> Personal auto insurance required</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">How Violations Affect Your Claim</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-600">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-red-500 font-bold">‚ö†</span>
              <span>Driver with suspended license = Lyft may be liable for negligent hiring</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-red-500 font-bold">‚ö†</span>
              <span>Failed background check missed = Increased company liability</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-red-500 font-bold">‚ö†</span>
              <span>Uninsured driver = Lyft's coverage still applies during active rides</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-red-500 font-bold">‚ö†</span>
              <span>Vehicle inspection failure = Potential mechanical defect claims</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Urgent: Short Statute States -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-red-50">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="bg-red-100 border-l-4 border-red-500 p-6 rounded-r-xl mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-800 mb-2">‚ö†Ô∏è Act Fast: 1-Year Statute of Limitations</h2>
        <p class="text-red-700">
          If your Lyft accident occurred in Louisiana or Tennessee, you have only <strong>ONE YEAR</strong> to file a claim. Don't wait!
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        {urgentStates.map(state => (
          <a href={`/states/${state.slug}/`} class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow hover:shadow-lg transition flex items-center gap-4">
            <div class="text-4xl">‚è∞</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-bold text-lg">{state.name}</h3>
              <p class="text-red-600 font-semibold">Only 1 year to file your Lyft accident claim!</p>
            </div>
          </a>
        ))}
      </div>
      
      <div class="mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/resources/statute-of-limitations/" class="text-secondary font-semibold hover:underline">
          View all state deadlines ‚Üí
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Top Lyft Markets -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-4">Top Lyft Markets We Serve</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 text-center mb-12">Find experienced Lyft accident lawyers in major cities</p>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-5 gap-4">
        {topMarkets.map(city => (
          <a href={`/cities/${city.slug}/`} class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-xl hover:bg-secondary hover:text-white transition group">
            <h3 class="font-bold">{city.name}</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 group-hover:text-white/80">{city.stateAbbr}</p>
          </a>
        ))}
      </div>
      
